cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically in the area of object detection and pose estimation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of physics simulation for generating training data indicates the category cs.RO (Robotics). The joint registration of multiple objects involves graph theory, which suggests the category cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves the use of multiple sub-tasks, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
